---
import Layout from '../layouts/main.astro';
---

<Layout title="Federal Sick Leave Guide - FEREX">
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-4xl">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Federal Employee Sick Leave Guide</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
        Understanding how sick leave impacts your federal retirement benefits
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-blue-900">Quick Summary</h2>
        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
          <p class="text-lg mb-2">
            <strong>Key Fact:</strong> Approximately <span class="text-blue-700 font-bold">2,087 hours of sick leave = 1 year of service credit</span>
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Your unused sick leave converts to service time, which <strong>increases your pension</strong> once you're eligible to retire. However, sick leave doesn't grant early retirement eligibility - you still need to meet age and service requirements.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-blue-900">Key Strategies</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-green-50 rounded-r">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-green-900">
              1. Sick Leave for Increased Pension (If Eligible)
            </h3>
            <p class="mb-3"><strong>Benefit:</strong> Your unused sick leave converts to service time, increasing your high-3 average salary calculation, leading to a larger annuity.</p>

            <p class="mb-3"><strong>How it Works:</strong> Roughly 2,087 hours of sick leave (40 hours/week × 52.14 weeks) equals one extra year of service, boosting your pension multiplier. For example, this can help you hit the 1.1% FERS multiplier at age 62 with less actual service time.</p>

            <p><strong>Action:</strong> Plan to save sick leave and avoid using it for routine time off; use annual leave for payouts instead.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-purple-50 rounded-r">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-900">
              2. Disability Retirement (If Medically Unable)
            </h3>
            <p class="mb-3"><strong>Benefit:</strong> If you're disabled for your job and it's expected to last a year, you can retire early under FERS Disability, even without full age/service, with a minimum of 18 months of FERS service.</p>

            <p class="mb-3"><strong>How it Works:</strong> Your agency must certify you can't do your job and can't be accommodated; excessive leave usage can help demonstrate this deficiency.</p>

            <p><strong>Action:</strong> Use Leave Without Pay (LWOP) for disability, which can support your claim, and work with OPM.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-blue-900">Steps to Take</h2>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">✓ Check Eligibility</h3>
            <p>Contact your agency's HR or Shared Services Center to verify your specific age and service time requirements.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">✓ Plan Leave Usage</h3>
            <p>Strategically use annual leave for payouts and save sick leave for pension enhancement or disability claims.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">✓ Apply for Retirement</h3>
            <p>Submit the <strong>"Application for Immediate Retirement" (SF 3107 for FERS)</strong> with your desired retirement date.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">✓ Consult HR</h3>
            <p>Your HR office provides personalized help with your records and annuity start dates.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-orange-900">Important Note</h2>
        <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-orange-900 mb-3">
            Sick leave helps you retire <em>better</em>, not <em>earlier</em> in terms of eligibility.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            You must meet OPM's age and service requirements for immediate retirement, or qualify for Disability Retirement. Sick leave credit is added to your service computation for pension calculation purposes only - it does not count toward meeting the initial eligibility requirements for retirement.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-blue-900">Example Calculation</h2>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Scenario: Federal Employee with 2,087 Hours of Sick Leave</h3>

          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between py-2 border-b">
              <span class="font-medium">Actual Service:</span>
              <span>29 years</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between py-2 border-b">
              <span class="font-medium">Sick Leave Credit:</span>
              <span>2,087 hours = 1 year</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between py-2 border-b bg-blue-100 px-3 -mx-3 rounded">
              <span class="font-bold">Total Service for Pension:</span>
              <span class="font-bold">30 years</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between py-2">
              <span class="font-medium">Impact:</span>
              <span class="text-green-700">May qualify for MRA+30 immediate retirement with full benefits</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-blue-900">Using FEREX to Plan</h2>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6">
          <p class="mb-4">In the <a href="/ferex" class="text-blue-700 font-semibold hover:underline">FEREX retirement calculator</a>, you can enter your unused sick leave hours in the control panel (left side of the dashboard).</p>

          <p class="mb-4">The calculator will automatically:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Convert your sick leave hours to years of service credit</li>
            <li>Add this credit to your total service computation</li>
            <li>Calculate your enhanced pension amount</li>
            <li>Show you the financial benefit of preserving your sick leave</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="mt-6">
            <a href="/ferex" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors">
              Try FEREX Calculator →
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-gray-900">Additional Resources</h2>

        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="border-l-4 border-gray-400 pl-4 py-2">
            <p class="font-semibold">OPM Retirement Services</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Official guidance on federal retirement benefits</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-gray-400 pl-4 py-2">
            <p class="font-semibold">Form SF 3107</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Application for Immediate Retirement (FERS)</p>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-4 border-gray-400 pl-4 py-2">
            <p class="font-semibold">Your Agency HR Office</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Personalized guidance based on your specific situation</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-300 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
        <p class="text-sm text-yellow-900">
          <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide provides general information about federal sick leave benefits. Individual circumstances vary, and you should consult with your agency's HR office and OPM for personalized advice regarding your specific situation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
